Alright guys, the first type of liquidity that we're going to go over is session liquidity

01:11.120 --> 01:12.120
Why is this important?

01:12.120 --> 01:16.920
It's because price often reacts very strongly to previous session highs and lows

01:16.920 --> 01:20.720
This is where the major high and major lows are going to be of each session

01:20.880 --> 01:22.880
For example, on the left side here you can see we have Asian session

01:22.880 --> 01:25.880
So you have the entire Asia session and you can see here's the major high

01:25.880 --> 01:26.880
And here's the major low

01:26.880 --> 01:30.880
There is going to be a lot of liquidity resting in both the high and the low

01:30.880 --> 01:32.880
And so for example when a new session starts

01:32.880 --> 01:35.880
You can see London session for example

01:35.880 --> 01:37.880
Once it sweeps Asia highs

01:37.880 --> 01:40.880
It'll typically get a reaction and then trade to maybe Asia lows

01:40.880 --> 01:42.880
