06:40.640 --> 06:42.640
Off of and trade the opposite direction from

06:42.640 --> 06:44.640
So for example here

06:44.640 --> 06:46.640
You could be taking longs towards this draw on liquidity

06:46.640 --> 06:48.640
Because we are in this bullish structure

06:48.640 --> 06:50.640
But then after that once we get that reaction

06:50.640 --> 06:52.640
Off of that liquidity pool we start forming

06:52.640 --> 06:54.640
Structure to validate a bearish bias right

06:54.640 --> 06:56.640
Then shorts could be valid

06:56.640 --> 06:58.640
A good practice to have every single morning

06:58.640 --> 07:00.640
Just going into your trading session would be

07:00.640 --> 07:02.640
To mark out something like previous day high and previous day low

07:02.800 --> 07:04.800
So you know the range that you are trading within

07:04.800 --> 07:06.800
Previous day high and previous day low is going to serve

07:06.800 --> 07:08.800
As an external liquidity point right

07:08.800 --> 07:10.800
These are never going to be your first TPs

07:10.800 --> 07:12.800
Previous session highs and previous session lows

07:12.800 --> 07:14.800
Previous day highs and previous day lows

07:14.800 --> 07:16.800
These shouldn't be your first TPs

07:16.800 --> 07:18.800
A general rule of thumb is that your first TPs should be internal liquidity

07:18.800 --> 07:20.800
Now previous day high and previous day low

07:20.800 --> 07:22.800
Like every other liquidity pool guys

07:22.800 --> 07:24.800
Doesn't necessarily have to get traded to right

07:24.800 --> 07:26.800
