Entry models later on but it's good to know

07:32.960 --> 07:34.960
Actually just what these draws on liquidity actually are

07:34.960 --> 07:36.960
Alright guys so for this next liquidity pool

07:36.960 --> 07:38.960
We have low resistance liquidity

07:38.960 --> 07:40.960
Also known as trend line liquidity

07:40.960 --> 07:42.960
Or you'll also hear it referred to as failure swings

07:42.960 --> 07:44.960
So this is known as trend line liquidity

07:44.960 --> 07:46.960
Because you can usually just draw a line

07:46.960 --> 07:48.960
And it will look like a trend line

07:48.960 --> 07:50.960
Now trend line liquidity is important

07:50.960 --> 07:52.960
Or LRL or failure swings

07:52.960 --> 07:54.960
Right this is what the books teach you right

07:54.960 --> 07:56.960
Every time you hit this line right here

07:56.960 --> 07:58.960
These people are going long and they are placing their stop losses where

07:59.120 --> 08:01.120
Well at these swings

08:01.120 --> 08:03.120
This is also called a failure swing

08:03.120 --> 08:05.120
Because it's not taking the recent low

08:05.120 --> 08:07.120
As you can see here we make a low

08:07.120 --> 08:09.120
We make a high, we make a higher low

08:09.120 --> 08:11.120
We don't make a lower low we make a higher low

08:11.120 --> 08:13.120
Then we have another high, higher low

08:13.120 --> 08:15.120
So these are all failure swings because they are not taking that recent low

08:15.120 --> 08:17.120
And every time this trend line

08:17.120 --> 08:19.120
Is getting hit

08:19.120 --> 08:21.120
There is going to be stop losses placed there

08:21.120 --> 08:23.120
In other words if you refer back to our last liquidity video

08:23.120 --> 08:25.120
We went over buy side liquidity and sell side liquidity

08:25.120 --> 08:27.120
So if we are generating

08:27.280 --> 08:29.280
Low resistance liquidity in bullish order flow

08:29.280 --> 08:31.280
What are we generating

08:31.280 --> 08:33.280
We are generating a bunch of sell side liquidity

08:33.280 --> 08:35.280
Right

08:35.280 --> 08:37.280
We have price continuing to run higher

08:37.280 --> 08:39.280
But failing to take out the previous low

08:39.280 --> 08:41.280
So what do we have amongst all these lows

08:41.280 --> 08:43.280
More sell side liquidity

08:43.280 --> 08:45.280
And so when you have all this sell side liquidity

08:45.280 --> 08:47.280
Just bunched up together

08:47.280 --> 08:49.280
That creates low resistance liquidity

08:49.280 --> 08:51.280
Same applies for a bearish sense right

08:51.280 --> 08:53.280
If we are trending bearish

08:53.280 --> 08:55.280
We can mark out this trend line liquidity

08:55.440 --> 08:57.440
Then we can see here that amongst all these

08:57.440 --> 08:59.440
Failure swings

08:59.440 --> 09:01.440
We have what, buy side liquidity

09:01.440 --> 09:03.440
And so we have a bunch of buy side

09:03.440 --> 09:05.440
Being generated amongst this trend line

09:05.440 --> 09:07.440
Therefore creating low resistance liquidity

09:07.440 --> 09:09.440
So now let's actually look at this on the chart

09:09.440 --> 09:11.440
Alright guys as you can see right here

09:11.440 --> 09:13.440
We have bullish trend line liquidity

09:13.440 --> 09:15.440
Bullish low resistance liquidity

09:15.440 --> 09:17.440
Now why is this low resistance liquidity

09:17.440 --> 09:19.440
Because there are failure swings being made

09:19.440 --> 09:21.440
At every single swing point

09:21.440 --> 09:23.440
Meaning that every time we make a swing high

09:23.600 --> 09:25.600
Every swing high is not taking that previous swing high

09:25.600 --> 09:27.600
So we just keep making these lower highs

09:27.600 --> 09:29.600
So as you can see here we have a swing high

09:29.600 --> 09:31.600
There's stop losses being rested here

09:31.600 --> 09:33.600
We have another swing high, stop losses being rested here

09:33.600 --> 09:35.600
More swing highs, stop losses are being rested here

09:35.600 --> 09:37.600
And these stop losses aren't getting taken

09:37.600 --> 09:39.600
Right, so they just keep getting generated

09:39.600 --> 09:41.600
Keep getting generated

09:41.600 --> 09:43.600
This is also known as generated liquidity

09:43.600 --> 09:45.600
You'll hear often times

09:45.600 --> 09:47.600
And then eventually the market likes to take out these

09:47.600 --> 09:49.600
Stop losses usually really fast

09:49.600 --> 09:51.600
We usually see super fast movement

09:51.760 --> 09:53.760
Through all of these swing highs

09:53.760 --> 09:55.760
Through all of these stop losses

09:55.760 --> 09:57.760
And that's exactly what the market does right here

09:57.760 --> 09:59.760
So in really simple words

09:59.760 --> 10:01.760
Just look for bunched up highs or bunched up lows

10:01.760 --> 10:03.760
That's going to be your low resistance liquidity

10:03.760 --> 10:05.760
If we pair this with a little bit of previous concepts here

10:05.760 --> 10:07.760
You can see that before price ran this low resistance liquidity

10:07.760 --> 10:09.760
We went ahead and swept some sell side

10:09.760 --> 10:11.760
We react off that sell side

10:11.760 --> 10:13.760
And then price goes ahead and rips through all this LR

10:13.760 --> 10:15.760
And typically it will run through all the LR

10:15.760 --> 10:17.760
Rather than just the first swing high

10:17.760 --> 10:19.760
And that is something you should really know

10:19.920 --> 10:21.920
Because low resistance liquidity in general

10:21.920 --> 10:23.920
Is a pretty obvious draw on liquidity

10:23.920 --> 10:25.920
Especially on the lower timeframes

10:25.920 --> 10:27.920
So definitely make sure you can understand

10:27.920 --> 10:29.920
The concept of low resistance liquidity

10:29.920 --> 10:31.920
Because if you're able to spot it

10:31.920 --> 10:33.920
You're going to be able to take trades targeting the low resistance liquidity

10:33.920 --> 10:35.920
Just think about it like a bunch of stop losses

10:35.920 --> 10:37.920
Ready to get ran through

